    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#GVCyr"/> <citedRange>053</citedRange></bibl>.</bibl>
                   </p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/> 
                        <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <space quantity="3" unit="character"/>
                        <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg real="+--|+"><w lemma="εὐπάτωρ"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">εὐ</supplied>πατόρων</w></seg> 
                        <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><space quantity="3" unit="character"/>
                    </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="2"><lem><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">εὐ</supplied>πατόρων</lem>
                <rdg><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">προ</supplied>πατόρων <note>J.M. Reynolds' suggestion</note></rdg>
                </app>
                </p>     
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
                <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> de nobles pères <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> with noble fathers <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> di nobili padri <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>No date was suggested by J.M. Reynolds in her notebook and no image is available. The date remains thus unknown.</p>
                <p>The very faint clue for interpreting this small fragment as from a verse epitaph is the poetic character of compounds in <foreign xml:lang="grc">-πάτωρ</foreign>. If ever this is right, <foreign xml:lang="grc">εὐπατόρων</foreign> should be preferred 
                on metrical grounds.</p>
                <p>Metrical analysis: a dactylic segment.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
